31
00:04:34,540 --> 00:04:35,800
Congratulations!

32
00:04:37,400 --> 00:04:42,020
By the way, the /oʊ/ sound is most often represented by the letter 'o,'

33
00:04:42,460 --> 00:04:46,820
so when you hear this sound, you may assume that it should be written with this letter.

34
00:04:48,340 --> 00:04:49,860
More on the spelling:

35
00:04:51,320 --> 00:04:55,840
The /oʊ/ sound is written as the letter 'o' in 80% of cases.

36
00:04:56,940 --> 00:05:01,640
The remaining 20% are split between the following combination of letters:

37
00:05:02,700 --> 00:05:05,440
'ow,' as in the word "snow,"

38
00:05:05,820 --> 00:05:08,080
'oa,' as in the word "coat,"

39
00:05:09,080 --> 00:05:11,480
'ou,' as in the word "though,"

40
00:05:11,940 --> 00:05:14,600
and 'ew,' as in the word "sew."

41
00:05:15,980 --> 00:05:18,740
We, too, like the spelling of the last combination! :).

